    "Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS) are essential for detecting attacks and anomalies in FL through host-based (Lee et al. 2021), signature-based, and network-based monitoring (Wu et al. 2020).",
    "A comparison of these methods is discussed in Table 3.",
    "However, AI-based IDS can detect unknown or zero-day attacks using adaptive resonance theory (Bukhanov and Polyakov 2018), genetic algorithms (Yunwu 2009; Ghani et al. 2024b), clustering, fuzzy logic (Dave and Sharma 2014), and deep learning models.",
